## Code Conventions

- Python 3.12+
- Type hints on all function signatures
- Google-style docstrings on public functions
- Use `pathlib.Path` for file operations, never `os.path`
- Use `dataclasses` or `pydantic` models for structured data
- Prefer `ruff` rules over manual style enforcement

## Testing Conventions

- Use `pytest` fixtures in `conftest.py` for shared setup
- Use `@pytest.mark.parametrize` for input variations
- Name test files `test_<module>.py`, test functions `test_<behavior>`
- Keep tests focused: one assertion concept per test

